	  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

		<introduction>
			<para>
				The Double Agent installation files are Microsoft Installer (MSI) packages. They can be installed
				using the <application>msiexec</application> program that&#39;s	part of <token>Windows</token>.
			</para>
		</introduction>
		<section>
			<title>Examples</title>
			<content>
				<para>
					Here are some sample command-lines (refer to Microsoft&#39;s MSI documentation
					for more details):
				</para>
				<list class="bullet">
					<listItem>
						<para>Install on a 64-bit system with the full user interface:</para>
						<para>
							<command>
								msiexec <system>/i</system> DoubleAgent_x64x86.msi
							</command>
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>Install on a 32-bit system with only a progress indicator and no user interaction:</para>
						<para>
							<command>
								msiexec <system>/i</system> DoubleAgent_x86.msi <system>/qb-!</system>
							</command>
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>Install with a progress indicator and cancel button, and a confirmation dialog at the end:</para>
						<para>
							<command>
								msiexec <system>/i</system> DoubleAgent_x86.msi <system>/qb+</system>
							</command>
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>Install with emulation enabled and only a confirmation dialog at the end:</para>
						<para>
							<command>
								msiexec <system>/i</system> DoubleAgent_x86.msi <system>/qn+</system> AUTO_EMULATE=1
							</command>
						</para>
					</listItem>
				</list>
			</content>
		</section>
		<section>
			<content>
				<para>
					If you configure your installation to automatically install Double Agent, you must include the appropriate
					Open Source acknowledgement (see <link xlink:href="e08466b9-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2" />).
				</para>
				<para>
					If you choose to deploy Double Agent with less than the full user interface, you should include some
					kind reference to the GNU license agreement in your installation. The GNU licenses in HTML format
					are included in the Double agent installation.
				</para>
			</content>
		</section>

